<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROPOSITION 111 PROS AND CONS AND ENDING TRAFFIC GRIDLOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ironically, we are faced with a situation where gridlock isn't slowing us down 
but actually speeding up our arrival with disaster. 
</P>
<P>
It is time we focus our energies towards solutions instead of creative ways to 
occupy our time while stuck in traffic. 
</P>
<P>
I can't count how many times I've longed to be on a commuter train, reading, 
rather than inhaling pollutants from hundreds of cars around me. My eyes and 
lungs burn to the point of having to keep my windows shut. 
</P>
<P>
Props. 111 and 108 are solutions that will produce noticeable results from our 
conscious efforts. I intend to vote yes on Props. 111 and 108. 
</P>
<P>
ALYCIA ANDERSON 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
