<P>
Piscopo, Miller Beer Rapped: A New York federal judge has rapped Miller Brewing 
Co., its ad agency and comedian Joe Piscopo by refusing to dismiss a copyright 
infringement suit against them brought by the Fat Boys rap group. At issue is a 
nationally-broadcast Miller Brewing television commercial featuring Piscopo and 
three Fat Boys look-alikes performing in the group's distinctive style. The Fat 
Boys had refused to appear in the ad, and U.S. District Judge Charles Haight 
said Miller and Piscopo exercised "bad faith and evasive motive" by copying the 
group. GREG BRAXTON 
