<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN MARCOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies are investigating what appears to be the murder-suicide of a 
67-year-old man and his 65-year-old ex-wife in the man's mobile home in San 
Marcos. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies Wednesday found the body of Ruth Estella Klauer on the living-room 
floor and that of Ernest Hall on the bed in the master bedroom. 
</P>
<P>
Hall had a revolver in his hand. 
</P>
<P>
About 5:30 p.m. Wednesday, deputies were summoned to the mobile home in the 
1900 block of San Marcos Boulevard by neighbors because a car was parked in the 
driveway, but lights in the home had been on for a few days. 
</P>
<P>
Klauer lived in the 3600 block of Village Circle in Carlsbad. 
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation indicated that Hall shot his ex-wife, then himself, 
sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
