<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 21-year-old San Diego motorist was shot in the left arm Thursday shortly 
after he left Interstate 5, in what police said was a random shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Eddie Newman had taken the Sassafrass Street exit about 11:30 a.m. and was 
stopped at a traffic light with his arm hanging out the window. Suddenly, he 
felt pain just above his left elbow. He had been shot, police spokesman Bill 
Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Newman drove home, and relatives took him to Sharp Memorial Hospital, Robinson 
said. A hospital spokeswoman said Newman was in good condition and was 
scheduled to undergo surgery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
