<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Cessna 152 crash-landed on its approach to Montgomery Field Thursday evening, 
killing the pilot, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police Sgt. Jim Clear said details of the crash, which occurred shortly before 
6 p.m., were sketchy but that the plane went down on the east end of the 
runway, which is on the eastern side of the airport property. 
</P>
<P>
He said the victim, identified only as a male, died at the scene. There were no 
passengers, Clear said, and no one on the ground was injured. 
</P>
<P>
"The plane was pretty scrunched up," he said, "but there was no fire at all 
from the crash." 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was unclear, and Federal Aviation Administration 
investigators were still examining the wreckage late Wednesday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
