<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-LAWMAKER 'POINTS' THE WAY TO CABINET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Veterans Affairs Secretary Edward J. Derwinski told former House colleagues 
Thursday that pointing the way to a restroom could lead to a Cabinet post. 
</P>
<P>
The former Illinois congressman told how 22 years ago he ran into a "freshman 
Republican congressman by the name of George Bush." 
</P>
<P>
"I didn't know him; he didn't know me," Derwinski said. "But he said: 'By the 
way, where's the men's room?' " Derwinski pointed the way, and Bush "was 
forever grateful for that help." 
</P>
<P>
"That's how you get to the Cabinet, fellows," said Derwinski, during a ceremony 
where he received the distinguished service award from the Assn. of Former 
Members of Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
