Great Western May Buy CenTrust: Great Western Financial in Beverly Hills is one 
of seven financial institutions reportedly interested in buying failed CenTrust 
Bank in Miami. Great Western agreed last year to buy CenTrust's branches, but 
the deal fell apart after regulators seized CenTrust in February. Other 
institutions reportedly interested in CenTrust include NCNB Corp. and First 
Union Corp., both of North Carolina; Citicorp in New York; Barnett Banks in 
Florida, and two Georgia banks, Sun-Trust Banks and Citizens &amp; Southern 
Corp. Great Western declined to comment. 
