</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Money Supply Mixed: The Federal Reserve Board reported that the narrowest 
measure of the nation's money supply, known as M1, fell in the week ended May 7 
to a seasonally adjusted $805.5 billion from $805.7 billion. 
</P>
<P>
A broader measure, M2, rose to a seasonally adjusted $3,271.6 billion from 
$3,269.2 billion the previous week. M1 includes cash in circulation, deposits 
in checking accounts and non-bank travelers checks. M2 is M1 plus accounts such 
as savings deposits and money market mutual funds. 
</P>
