CONTRA AIDE SCORNS DEADLINE TO DISARM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A senior Contra rebel leader said the June 10 deadline for disarming the 
Nicaraguan insurgent force is "utopian" and that at least 10,000 rebels will 
still be armed on that date. Contra political leader Aristides Sanchez said a 
strike by Sandinista workers this week showed that President Violeta Barrios de 
Chamorro is not in full control of the government and could not guarantee the 
security of the disarmed rebels. "Whenever the Sandinistas want, they can 
paralyze the country," Sanchez said. 
