<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: NETWORKS LOSE BID FOR TAPES IN MENENDEZ 
CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Monica Superior Court Judge James A. Albracht on Thursday denied requests 
by the ABC and NBC television networks for potentially key evidence in the 
murders of Jose Menendez and his wife, Kitty. 
</P>
<P>
Albracht tentatively rejected making public an audiotape of an emergency 911 
telephone call made to police last Aug. 20, when the Menendez couple was found 
slain in their Beverly Hills mansion. 
</P>
<P>
He said he would reconsider his decision next Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The judge also rebuffed attempts by the networks to gain video and audiotapes 
made during the seizure of evidence in a Beverly Hills psychologist's office, 
and information dealing with the purchase of two shotguns that are believed by 
police to be the possible murder weapons. 
</P>
<P>
Albracht has ordered the county coroner to make public autopsy reports on the 
slain couple. On Thursday, on a motion by the Los Angeles Daily Journal 
newspaper, he ordered the coroner to make public investigative and 
toxicological reports as well. 
</P>
</TEXT>
