<P>
LOOKIN' GOOD: Artisans in Dublin, Tex., have finished refurbishing the county 
airport's nine-foot statue of John Wayne, and they say he's looking better than 
ever. . . . Years of pigeons and ocean air had turned Duke a dark, unflattering 
green -- all except the hand tourists hold while posing for snapshots. . . . 
Acids have been applied to create "lifelike" shades of skin and apparel. . . . 
Duke may return next month, but he won't appear publicly until the new terminal 
opens this fall (B1). Mark I. Pinsky and Jan Herman 
</P>
