<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Irvine Sensors Corp.: The Costa Mesa developer of infrared devices and computer 
electronics reported a second-quarter loss of $165,900, contrasted with a 
year-earlier loss of $262,500. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue for the quarter ended April 1 rose 22% to $869,700 from $710,200. For 
the six-month period, the company lost $307,300, contrasted with a loss of 
$456,500 a year earlier. Revenue increased 29% to $1.8 million from $1.4 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
