<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marine National Bank: The Irvine bank said its first-quarter earnings declined 
28% to $139,261 from $192,725 a year earlier. The bank attributed the decline 
to a tax increase and a 4% increase in operating expenses. Total assets were up 
5% to $82.7 million from $78.5 million. 
</P>
