<HEADLINE>
<P>
'SNL' WITH CLAY WINDS UP FOURTH IN NATIONAL RATINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It looks as if wholesome can still beat outrageous, even on "Saturday Night 
Live." 
</P>
<P>
NBC said Thursday that despite the impressive overnight ratings for the 
controversial appearance by comedian Andrew Dice Clay last weekend, the final 
national figures showed that the program was only the fourth highest rated 
edition of this season. The first? The one hosted by Fred Savage of ABC's "The 
Wonder Years." 
</P>
<P>
The Clay installment had garnered "Saturday Night Live's" best ratings of the 
season in the 23 large cities that deliver overnight figures, but the numbers 
did not hold up in the smaller markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
