<P>
21 ABOARD PLANE, 4 IN HOME DIE IN CRASH AFTER TAKEOFF IN MANILA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A twin-engine inter-island plane crashed and exploded in a fireball in a Manila 
suburb today, killing all 21 people aboard and burning to death a family of 
four inside their home, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The propeller-driven Beechcraft 1900 aircraft went into a spin as it fell two 
minutes after takeoff from Manila's airport. 
</P>
<P>
It slammed into the main bedroom of a house leased by a Japanese businessman, 
engulfing it in flames and scattering debris and bodies over a wide area. 
</P>
<P>
The plane's burning tail came to rest by the family swimming pool. The rest of 
the aircraft exploded in pieces. 
</P>
<P>
Just before the crash, the pilot radioed the control tower that he was turning 
back because his right engine had cut out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
