P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
MURDOCH TO SELL SHARES IN POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONG KONG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newspaper tycoon Rupert Murdoch, whose News Corp. posted a dramatic 74% drop in 
nine-month net profit this week, is planning to raise cash by selling some 
shares in his Hong Kong daily, the South China Morning Post, market sources 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Murdoch, who gained full control of the Post in 1986 by buying up the publicly 
traded shares and then taking the listing off the local stock exchange, stands 
to get a cash injection of $166 million if the float succeeds. 
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Post declined to comment, as did the Hong Kong and Shanghai 
Banking Corp.'s wholly owned merchant banking arm, Wardley Capital Limited, 
identified by the sources as co-lead arranger of the deal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
