<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
B. B. KING TV FILM PREMIERES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANOLA, Miss. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A documentary of blues man B. B. King's life, produced for the British 
Broadcasting Co.'s "Omnibus" television series, had its world premiere in his 
hometown. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from $10 ticket sales for the one-hour film will go to Indianola's 
parks. 
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 people turned out for the film, which was shown at the Mid-Delta 
Arts Assn. theater. The film has yet to be broadcast in England. 
</P>
<P>
Much of the film about the blues musician was filmed in Indianola. Many scenes 
of last year's concert in Fletcher Park are included, as are local landmarks 
and citizens. The film reviews King's childhood in Indianola. 
</P>
<P>
King is giving a benefit concert June 1, with proceeds going to parks in the 
town of 8,200 residents in west-central Mississippi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
