</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Beatle Paul McCartney gained a spot in the Guinness Book of World 
Records for the largest paid attendance at a public event, his publicist said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
McCartney and his band performed for a crowd of 184,000 at the Maracana Stadium 
in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, on April 21. 
</P>
<P>
He broke the record of 175,000 set by Frank Sinatra at the stadium on Jan. 26, 
1980. 
</P>
<P>
The Guinness Book acknowledged the record early this month, said Mika El-Baz, 
McCartney's New York publicist. 
</P>
